@*
    Help documentation view for PcApprovalHistory component.
    Provides user documentation explaining the approval history timeline functionality.
*@

<div class="pc-approval-history-help">
    <h4><i class="fas fa-history"></i> Approval History Component</h4>
    
    <p>
        The <strong>Approval History</strong> component displays a timeline of all actions taken on an approval request.
        It provides a comprehensive audit trail showing the complete lifecycle of the approval process.
    </p>
    
    <h5>Timeline Information</h5>
    <p>Each entry in the timeline displays the following information:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Action Type</strong> - The type of action performed:
            <ul>
                <li><i class="fas fa-paper-plane text-primary"></i> <em>Submitted</em> - Request was initially submitted for approval</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-check text-success"></i> <em>Approved</em> - Request was approved by an approver</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-times text-danger"></i> <em>Rejected</em> - Request was rejected by an approver</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-share text-info"></i> <em>Delegated</em> - Request was delegated to another user</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-arrow-up text-warning"></i> <em>Escalated</em> - Request was escalated due to timeout or manual escalation</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>User</strong> - The name of the user who performed the action</li>
        <li><strong>Timestamp</strong> - The date and time when the action was performed</li>
        <li><strong>Comments</strong> - Any comments or notes provided by the user during the action (if applicable)</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h5>Configuration Options</h5>
    <table class="table table-sm table-bordered">
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Option</th>
                <th>Type</th>
                <th>Description</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td><code>request_id</code></td>
                <td>Datasource Binding</td>
                <td>
                    Binds to the ID of the approval request whose history should be displayed.
                    This can be bound to a page datasource, URL parameter, or a record field containing
                    the approval request GUID.
                </td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
    
    <h5>Usage</h5>
    <p>
        Add this component to any page where you want to display the approval history for a specific request.
        Configure the <code>request_id</code> option to bind to the appropriate datasource that provides
        the approval request identifier.
    </p>
    
    <h5>Notes</h5>
    <ul>
        <li>The timeline is displayed in reverse chronological order (most recent actions first)</li>
        <li>If no history records exist for the specified request, an informational message is shown</li>
        <li>The component automatically refreshes when the page is reloaded</li>
    </ul>
</div>

